snippet: “Turbulence” is like an eight-ring circus with situations, both inconsequential and those charged with political meaning, erupting all over the stage.
abstract: Gia Kourlas reviews premiere of piece Turbulence (a dance about the economy), choreographed by Keith Hennessy, at New York Live Arts.
lead_paragraph: “Turbulence” is like an eight-ring circus with situations, both inconsequential and those charged with political meaning, erupting all over the stage.

headline.seo: Keith Hennessy’s ‘Turbulence’ at New York Live Arts
headline.main: Churning Their Way Through a Familiar Labyrinth of Economics and Politics
